# Cloudflare deployment

This app ships to **Cloudflare Workers** (`meal-prep` → https://meals.wheresharvey.com), not Vercel.

## How code goes live

1. **Preferred:** push to `main` → [Workers Builds](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/ci-cd/builds/) runs `npm run deploy`.
2. **Fallback:** from the repo root, run `npm run deploy` (requires Wrangler login).

Git push alone is not enough until Workers Builds is connected to `harveygerardMK/meal-prep`.

## After shipping user-facing changes

When the user asks to commit/push **or** expects production to update:

1. Push to `origin/main` if needed.
2. Confirm a Workers Build started (Cloudflare Builds MCP: set active worker `meal-prep` / id `271c613b6dfa4ca79841dcc92f92c418`, then list builds).
3. If Builds is not connected or no build appears, run `npm run deploy` and tell the user why.

## Build settings (dashboard)

| Setting | Value |
|---------|--------|
| Deploy command | `npm run deploy` |
| Build command | empty |
| Non-production | `npm run upload` |
| Production branch | `main` |

Do not use plain `npx wrangler deploy` as the Builds deploy command — this project needs `scripts/cloudflare-build.mjs` (OpenNext + proxy/middleware swap). Deployments must keep `--keep-vars` (already wired in that script).
